&\Rightarrow 0.7y = 153 - y \\
&\Rightarrow 1.7y = 153 \\
&\Rightarrow y = 153/1.7 \\
&\Rightarrow y = 90.
\end{align*}
Using this value of $y$, we can easily find the value of $x$.
\begin{align*}
x = 153 - y = 153 - 90 = 63.
\end{align*}
Finally, we can find the value of $y$ minus $x$.
\begin{align*}
y - x = 90 - 63 = \boxed{27}.
\end{align*}
